<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="screening">Screening</a> - A method to obtain a set of organisms <em>exempli gratia</em> a <a href="#bacterial_colony">bacterial colony</a>, with a particular <a href="#genotype">genotype</a> or <a href="#phenotype">phenotype</a> by considering many members of a large pool of variants. Each member is assessed for its suitability, causing more work than <a href="#selection">selection</a>, where the undesired members are eliminated.